        "Start with scaling in. You open with a starter, a third to half of your intended size, and you add the rest only once the trade confirms, when the price action is behaving, the first phase of the catalyst lands, and the thesis is visibly strengthening. The cardinal rule is that you add to winners and confirming theses only. Adding to a falling, broken trade is averaging down, which is a different episode and frankly a horror film.",
